\bibitem{footnote:anisotropy}
We observe that we do \emph{not} recover the elastic fluctuation free energy of Ref.~\cite{xgr} in the bulk limit. This is because we consider an elastomer which is of \emph{axisymmetric} form in its undeformed state, and thus remains anisotropic in the bulk limit, whereas Ref.~\cite{xgr} considered an elastomer which is \emph{spherical} when undeformed, and thus isotropic. 

